Author: paretoer
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: 2019 SEP 16 - An update to Pareto Network:  The platform is up & running you can access via the website using an Ethereum address containing any amount of PARETO.  Current Updates: 1) Pareto now has 3 pairs on LATOKEN exchange: PARETO/BTC & PARETO/ETH & PARETO/USDT 2) Pareto is now available on the newly launched Eterbase exchange: PARETO/ETH 3) Pareto is also available on DDEX : PARETO/USDC & IDEX: PARETO/ETH 4) Telegram official updates are currently available only at @ParetoNetworkOfficial  Upcoming Updates: 1- Token Swap from ERC20 to ERC777. The swap will make UX & adoption smoother. 2-  Introducing a trial version using a generalized organization maintained user. 3-  Institutional onboarding to the platform e.g Institutional Brokers & Family Offices. 4- Staking tokens to earn a portion of the reward pool. 5-  Governance via token ownership to vote on commission percentage & minimum score requirements. 6- Implementing a Minimum PARETO Score to use platform. 7- Content Contributor Dashboard. 8- Telegram Bot. 9- Onboarding for new users. 10- Open up network for adhoc content providers. 11- Launch Sentinels for content decentralization. 12- Upgrades to Organization Structure, Pareto Network Platform, Intel Smart Contact, PARETO Reward Asset towards the next versions. 13- Credit card purchases & checkout of PARETO tokens from the website. 14- BEP-2 for transferability on Binance Chain, and support other atomic swap protocols and network.

The Ecosystem will provide incentives and a mechanism for a wide range of individuals and organizations to create and share this information and subsequently receive compensation for their effort.

Author: carnitastaco
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: The information is curated & structured by the network, and then distributed to token owners in a prioritized sequence. An algorithm is used to determine the order in which Pareto token holders are presented with the information. The result of this algorithm is called the Information Waterfall. By ranking higher in the Waterfall, a token holder can act on valuable information before people that follow, giving her a significant advantage.

Author: 23coins
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: And who can participate to your project?

Author: elrugrim
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: Content contributors may be individuals, groups or organizations. They may generate single items of information or multiple items produced over time.

Author: 23coins
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: How does the ranking algorithm is working for participants?

Author: elrugrim
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: In its simplest form, the algorithm is counting how many Pareto tokens a user owns, how long they’ve held tokens, and how many Pareto tokens they have spent by paying content contributors. The largest benefit comes from spending the tokens on content contributors, creating a virtuous circle of incentivized information that benefits the users of Pareto tokens. The algorithm penalizes speculative purchases of the tokens.

Author: 23coins
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: And what about rewards?

Author: elrugrim
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: Rewards have a cost in Pareto tokens, set by Content Contributors, and this cost is rewarded directly to the Content Contributor. If the user rewards the total cost set by the Content Contributor, he will receive the full power of the reward and move up the waterfall appropriately. If the user rewards less than the amount requested by the content contributor, he will move up proportionally to the amount contributed.

Author: Groc
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: The information is curated & structured by the network, and then distributed to token owners in a prioritized sequence. An algorithm is used to determine the order in which Pareto token holders are presented with the information. The result of this algorithm is called the Information Waterfall. By ranking higher in the Waterfall, a token holder can act on valuable information before people that follow, giving her a significant advantage.

Author: paretonetwork
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: The content creators have to figure out what resonates with the network to obtain the maximum yield. This is no different than formatting something in the relevant way for an ebay listing, or a craigslist post, if you do it wrong then nobody will pay attention to it.  For some time, we will be subsidizing selected content contributors from our company treasury, as they learn how to provide the best information  Also, do note that people will always be adjusting their rank, so some ranking adjustments may actually be frivolous and unrelated to the quality of the information, yet result in the content contributor being paid

Author: paretonetwork
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: We are very different than "prediction markets".  The white paper answers this  https://pareto.network/download/Pareto-Technical-White-Paper.pdf   "Prediction markets rely on the wisdom of the crowd, promoting a binary side bet that something will or will not happen, or that opposites will happen. It is meant to aggregate all available information to determine what team will win, who will win an election, and other forms of binary events. The purpose is to create a limited incentive for people to put money behind a decision they believe in. The limitation comes from both the kinds of information that can be applicable to a prediction market, and the information available to the crowd to begin with. Finally, markets may not form at all outside of the biggest events already in the collective conscious, exacerbating an already irreconcilable liquidity problem. There are many circumstances to suggest that there is no wisdom of the crowd, such as in the options markets and in elections, yet prediction markets do not provide a liquid enough venue to make contrarian decisions. The liquidity concern is proportionate to the funds available to other bettors, whereas expert provided information is the only form of liquidity in the Pareto Network. The cryptocurrency financial markets are not transparent enough for the whole market to make rational decisions, and the market participants are not rational to begin with. The market consistently discounts improbable situations, and this is reflected in prediction markets. The Pareto Network provides an incentive to disclose the improbable. This results in enabling as many people as possible to make profitable investment decisions in the relevant markets before non-users, based on real-time information they obtain from the Pareto Network. The users are in turn incentivized to compensate the Content Contributors with Pareto tokens, as that action improves their ranking on the Pareto leaderboard and allows those people to get the next information disclosure sooner."

Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: Users are ranking by how active they are in the network.  The system looks at number of Pareto owned, the average length of time they've been owned, and how often they have rewarded content contributors  The last variable is the most important to the ranking. A user can get an exponentially higher ranking from rewarding than compared to just buying a bunch of Pareto tokens.

Author: paretonetwork
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: Content contributors get paid when users find it valuable enough. If a content contributor posts poor quality information then they would have spent some Pareto tokens and nobody on the network would reward it.  Users gain an increased ranking when they reward a content contributor. Increased ranking gets them access to new content faster, and they'll only do that if they find information valuable.  Therefore in reality, a content contributor's maximum payout for each piece of content is proportional to the number of users that want a higher rank. But users won't reward just anything, they will choose which content contributors are making them money so they can keep buying Pareto.  We will be announcing one of our first key content contributors soon.

Author: skybot13x
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: Spreading valuable information which helps you beating the market usually wouldn't get shared. And if it gets shared there might still be egoistic motives involved. If a bank labels an asset a buy, the bank isn't really interested in making you money. The bank is interested in making money for itself by either creating orchestrated herd behavior for a specific asset or by selling shit which they say is buy. I am curious to see how a platform like yours could work in the end (if at all). Our whole lives are about information tied to assets and most human beings don't feel like sharing the stuff that really makes you money.

Author: paretonetwork
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: The value you can earn in Pareto can be greater than the value you can earn from trying to trade on the information yourself.  In the Pareto Network the incentive models are aligned better.  Our white paper goes into more detail about who would use it, why they would use it over doing something else, and under what circumstances our network is a better way to make money, in the "case studies" section.  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j6MFoSQkT7U

Author: paretonetwork
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: Our marketing is very expansive, and we have several press releases coming out related to who our initial content contributors are, as well as information within the Pareto Network which would have garnered users great profits if they were signed up.

Author: paretonetwork
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: We are working on a GUI right now. The network can actually be access via command line and REST API as is, but this isn't what we want to demo to users and presale purchasers.  There will be a primary Web app, a Telegram chat bot, and we are pursuing leveraging the STATUS network's mobile interfaces to deliver content to users, Eidoo's mobile interfaces, as well as a Pareto-branded mobile app  The primary goal is to simply allow users to gain access to the network and receive information quickly, so that they are in a place to act on it before the rest of the market.  Our actual roadmap involves bring on more and more institutional financial firms as users, who aren't equipped to use cryptocurrency. Selling this solution conveniently to them at a premium is our business model.  Our presale purchasers will have initial access to the platform, and have a higher rank than the crowdsale purchasers, just because they were there earlier.

Author: paretonetwork
Title: [ANN][PRESALE] Pareto Network - The P2P Financial Content & Information Marketplace
Body: As stated the presale has a hardcap of 25,000 ETH or $12m  The first 20% of purchasers get a 10% bonus, this is determined when we distribute tokens after the sale      As a content contributor you would submit content to the Pareto Network with a small fee paid in their coin PXT.  Once the content is submitted, it is distributed to users in a prioritized order based on the ranking of the user.  The user then rewards the contributor in PXT based on the value they have received from the content.  You can learn more on our website: https://www.pareto.network/ Whitepaper: https://www.pareto.network/download/Pareto-Technical-White-Paper.pdf Contribute now: https://tokensale.pareto.network
